      "writtenOn": "2019-03-04T04:34:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Sorry, I\u0027m not aware of any other use of \"full\" in this context...\n\nWhile I\u0027ll defer to derat@, you may want to compose a sentense describing the attribute using the word \"full\". If I were to write one, I would: \"full set of Android systems, including unstable ones\". So I think \"android_full_set\" is OK (since \"full\" describes \"set\" here), while \"android_full\" is not since \"full\" looks to describe \"Android\" (makes me wonder \"what is full Android?\").",
      "parentUuid": "d6558a82_e433b580",
      "revId": "686a9e4f2db4dde5116992c3b8447461e4dcb879",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
